Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle over the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop the flesh out into a onto a #board{}. Chop into small chunks.

Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Remove the @pineapple rings{1} from the tin (keep the tin and juice for later) and cut into small chunks.

Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Pop the @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} into a #medium bowl{}. Add a squeeze of lime juice and season to taste with salt and pepper, adding more lime juice if needed. Add the tomatoes, pineapple chunks and avocado along with half the coriander. Mix together and set aside.

Pop the @soured cream{75%g} in a #small bowl{} and add the lime zest. Season with salt and pepper and mix together.

When your wedges have 5 mins remaining, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @king prawns{225%g} along with the @garlic{} and @Cajun Blackening{1}. Season with salt and pepper and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Then add @pineapple juice{1/2%tbsp} per person and stir-fry until the prawns are cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Pop your @plain taco tortillas{4} onto the middle shelf of your oven to warm through for the last ~{1-2%minutes} of wedge cooking time. Transfer your tortillas to plates and serve with a spoonful of zesty soured cream, spread over the bottom, followed by the prawns and salsa. Finish with the wedges alongside and the remaining coriander sprinkled over the top. Enjoy!